item.title: Book List
item.description: Preview You cannot read all books containing valuable information in a thousand lifetimes. The trick is knowing which ones to read. This list has the possibility of being modified over time. Books 12 Rules for Life: An Antidote to Chaos - Jordan Peterson Maps of Meaning: The Architecture of Belief - Jordan Peterson 48 Laws of Power - Robert Greene The Unplugged Alpha - Richard Cooper The Richest Man in Babylon - George Samuel Clason The Intelligent Investor - Benjamin Graham 1984 - George Orwell $100M Offers: How to Make Offers So Good People Feel Stupid Saying No - Alex Hormozi Brave New World - Aldous Huxley Road To Wigan Pier - George Orwell Crime And Punishment - Fyodor Dostoevsky Demons - Fyodor Dostoevsky Beyond Good And Evil - Friedrich Nietzsche Ordinary Men - Christopher Browning The Painted Bird - Jerzy Kosinski The Rape of Nanking - Iris Chang Gulag Archipelago (Vol.
